As Gill prepares for the England tour in June 2025, his leadership and MRF association mark a new chapter for Indian cricket.
title: Shubman Gill showcases unique sticker on MRF bat ahead of first Test as captain

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Senior Congress leader Jairam Ramesh has strongly criticised the United States for inviting Pakistan's army chief General Asim Munir to the US army day celebrations. Ramesh questioned the invitation, citing Munir's inflammatory remarks before the Pahalgam terror attacks. He also objected to US officials describing Pakistan as a counter-terrorism partner.
title: 'What is US really up to?' Jairam Ramesh slams US for inviting Munir

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Dominick McGee, once an obscure online figure, rose to prominence on X through controversial posts, even gaining White House access. He leveraged attention-grabbing tactics, like misgendering Brittney Griner, to boost his visibility. While X's revenue-sharing program initially proved lucrative, earnings became unpredictable.
title: Who is Dominick McGee? MAGA influencer stirring up outrage on X

author: MAHESH BUDDI
description: Anti-Corruption Bureau teams raided the residence of Nune Sridhar, a senior irrigation engineer involved in the Kaleshwaram Lift Irrigation Project, unearthing assets worth approximately ₹60 crore disproportionate to his known income sources. Sridhar, who previously supervised the Gayathri pump house, was arrested following searches at 14 locations across multiple cities. The raids occurred amidst an inquiry into alleged KLIP irregularities.
title: ‘Villa, flats, 19 plots, 16-acre land, gold, crores in bank’: Telangana engineer held

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold and silver price prediction: Gold prices are recovering, trading above a falling channel. Support is seen at ₹96,600, with a target of ₹99,000. Silver has broken resistance at ₹1,01,000 and is targeting ₹1,10,000. Support lies at ₹1,04,000.
title: Gold & silver price prediction today: Should you buy or sell?

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Elon Musk's net worth saw a rise. This happened after he apologized to Donald Trump. Musk regretted his social media posts. He had criticized Trump earlier. The apology followed a phone call. Trump acknowledged Musk's statement. The market reacted positively. Musk's wealth increased by $191 million. It reached $411.4 billion.
title: How this one-sentence by Elon Musk made him richer by $191 million

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Gautam Gambhir, the Indian cricket team's head coach, motivated the squad, including new captain Shubman Gill and debutants, during a pre-series nets session in Beckenham. He emphasised seizing the opportunity to create a memorable tour despite the absence of experienced players - Virat Kohli, Rohit Sharma and R Ashwin.
title: IND vs ENG: Gambhir discloses how India can have a 'memorable tour'; Gill shares approach

author: RAJAT PANDIT
description: Air Marshal Ashutosh Dixit highlighted India's Operation Sindoor, showcasing the effectiveness of long-range precision strikes that nullify geographical barriers. He emphasized the importance of real-time situational awareness and deep surveillance in modern conflicts.
title: Long-range precision weapons make geographical barriers irrelevant: Air Marshal Dixit

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former Australian cricketer Matthew Hayden criticized South Africa's lack of intent on day one of the WTC final against Australia, highlighting Bavuma's slow start. Sanjay Bangar emphasized Australia's strong position due to early wickets. Despite Smith and Webster's fifties, Rabada's five-wicket haul restricted Australia to 212.
title: Matthew Hayden criticises South Africa's approach against Australia

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tensions escalate as Israel prepares for a potential military operation against Iran. This move could disrupt diplomacy and trigger regional conflict. US intelligence suggests Iran is nearing nuclear weapon capability. Diplomatic talks are stalling. The US is bracing for Israeli action. Retaliatory strikes against US assets are a concern. Oil markets are reacting to the rising tensions.
title: Middle East: Is Israel ready to hit Iran's nuclear sites? US braces for fallout

author: TOI Education
description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) is expected to announce the NEET UG 2025 results soon, following the exam held on May 4. Over 22.7 lakh candidates appeared across 557 cities and 14 foreign centres. Results, along with key performance data and the final answer key, will be available online at neet.nta.nic.in.
title: NEET UG result : Expected announcement date revealed; steps to download scorecards

author: TOI TRENDING DESK
description: Khankhuuluu mongoliensis, or "Dragon Prince," a newly identified tyrannosauroid species, roamed Mongolia 86 million years ago. Initially misidentified, high-tech scans revealed this agile predator, weighing 750 kilos, predates T. rex. This discovery suggests tyrannosaurs possibly originated in Asia, migrated to North America, and then returned, reshaping our understanding of dinosaur evolution and distribution.
title: New dinosaur species 'Dragon Prince' discovered — what did it look like?

author: KAPIL DIXIT
description: A newlywed couple from Pratapgarh, Kaushlendra and Ankita, remain missing after their tourist vehicle plunged into the Teesta River in Sikkim thirteen days ago. The couple, married in May, were on their honeymoon when the accident occurred, leaving their families in distress.
title: No trace of newlywed Pratapgarh couple on honeymoon trip to Sikkim

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Paytm's stock price plummeted by 10% following the finance ministry's denial of plans to introduce Merchant Discount Rate (MDR) on UPI transactions, contradicting earlier media reports. The clarification triggered investor concerns, leading to Paytm's steepest single-day drop since February 2024. Payments Council of India had previously advocated for MDR to sustain digital payments infrastructure.
title: Paytm shares crash 10% after FinMin’s statement on UPI transactions; here’s what happened

author: NEEL KAMAL
description: Kamal Kaur, a well-known Instagram influencer from Ludhiana with over 3.83 lakh followers, was discovered dead in a car near Adesh Medical University in Bathinda on Thursday. Kaur was popular for her reels on Instagram. Police have initiated an investigation into the circumstances surrounding her death.
title: Punjab shocker: Popular social media influencer Kamal Kaur found dead in car; probe on

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A federal judge ordered the release of Mahmoud Khalil, a legal US resident detained after participating in pro-Palestinian demonstrations. The judge cited irreparable harm to Khalil's career and free speech rights due to his detention. Despite the ruling, Khalil will remain in custody pending a possible government appeal, highlighting ongoing legal battles over activism and immigration.
title: Deportation case: Federal judge orders release of Palestinian activist Mahmoud Khalil

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: The belief that fruit seeds cause appendicitis is largely a myth. Studies show seeds rarely contribute to the condition. Appendicitis is usually due to blockages or infections. Research indicates foreign objects can affect the appendix. Appendicitis and appendix cancer are distinct. Appendicitis is inflammation, not cancer. Sometimes, appendicitis surgery reveals hidden tumors.
title: Fact-check: Can fruit seeds pose a threat to the appendix?

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sanjana Ganesan revealed that Jasprit Bumrah's cricket has improved since their son Angad's birth, attributing it to a peaceful home life. She also highlighted the unique personalities of cricketers' wives and their complementary roles. Sanjana shared lighthearted moments with Bumrah, noting his attempts to distract her during interviews and their comfortable off-field bond as 'gossip buddies'.
title: 'I think he became a better cricketer': Sanjana Ganesan on Jasprit Bumrah

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Pranav Patel, an Indian-origin man, received a six-year prison sentence for his role in a fraud targeting senior citizens. He laundered $1,791,301, collected from elderly victims across the eastern US, who were deceived by overseas callers posing as US treasury officials. One victim even lost his home due to the scam.
title: Indian-origin man jailed in US; duped senior citizens as 'money mule'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump's attendance at the Kennedy Center's 'Les Misérables' opening was met with mixed reactions amidst his efforts to reshape the institution. Accompanied by Melania Trump and GOP allies, his visit coincided with reports of cast boycotts and followed his controversial overhaul of the center's leadership and proposed arts funding cuts.
title: Kennedy Center: Donald Trump and Melania cheered, booed; watch video

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Donald Trump indicated flexibility on extending the trade talk deadline. However, he believes it might not be essential. Discussions are ongoing with multiple countries. The US will soon send letters outlining final trade deal terms. A deal with China is reportedly done, pending final approval pending final approval from Trump  and Chinese President Xi Jinping
title: 'Take it or leave it': Trump may extend July 8 tariff deadline

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: England's head coach Brendon McCullum expressed excitement about the upcoming five-Test series against India, highlighting the team's varied bowling attack. Despite missing key bowlers, he praised the emerging talent, including spinner Shoaib Bashir. India, embarking on a new era without veterans like Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli, will begin their WTC cycle. Shubman Gill will be leading the side.
title: 'We know where we want to get to'- Brendon McCullum confident in England’s new bowling unit

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tokyo has lodged a strong protest with Beijing following a dangerous encounter between Chinese fighter jets and a Japanese patrol plane in the Pacific. The incident, occurring last weekend, involved Chinese jets flying within 45 meters of the Japanese aircraft.
title: 'Within 45 metres': Chinese fighter jets fly close to Japan military aircraft

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: Bengal clashes: Cops injured, security heightened- what triggered the outrage?

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: In Faridabad, Manoj Mehto took his four sons to railway tracks. He bought them chips and cola. Then, he held them firmly as the Golden Temple Express approached. The train ran them over, killing them all. Police are investigating the motive. Preeti, Manoj's wife, is left alone. Neighbors are shocked and offer condolences.
title: Faridabad family suicide horror: Parathas to plans for outing, calm before tragedy

author: TOI Education
description: The Maharashtra School Education and Sports Department has released the final general merit list for FYJC Class 11 admissions 2025 on mahafyjcadmissions.in. Following a revised timeline to accommodate grievance redressals, the list marks the beginning of zero-round admissions. Over 20 lakh seats across 9,281 colleges are on offer for Arts, Science, and Commerce streams.
title: Maharashtra FYJC general merit list released: Direct download link- what to do next

description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened flat in trade on Thursday, While Nifty50 opened above 25,150, BSE Sensex was above 82,500.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens flat; BSE Sensex above 82,500

description: Donald Trump's "Gold Card," offering a path to US citizenship for foreigners investing $5 million, has launched its waiting list. Trump announced the opening via social media, highlighting the immense interest.
title: Trump unveils US 'Gold Card' website: Who can apply, eligibility

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Kagiso Rabada's stunning five-wicket haul helped South Africa dismiss Australia for 212 on Day 1 of the WTC Final at Lord's. However, Australia fought back, leaving South Africa at 43 for 4 at stumps. The day also saw a historic first, with both teams' No. 1 batters dismissed for a duck.
title: WTC Final: History made after 145 years at Lord’s

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mitchell Starc etched his name in history at Lord's, becoming the leading wicket-taker in ICC tournament finals with 11 wickets, surpassing Mohammed Shami. Australia's pace attack, led by Starc, dismantled South Africa, leaving them reeling at 43 for 4 after being bowled out for 212. Kagiso Rabada's five-wicket haul and a rare statistical anomaly marked a day dominated by bowlers.
title: WTC Final: Mitchell Starc surpasses Mohammed Shami during Aus vs SA

description: Top stock market recommendations: Nuvama Professional Clients Group's Aakash K Hindocha recommends Tata Motors, Mphasis, and Hero Motocorp as top stock picks. Nifty is expected to reach 25400/25600, while Bank Nifty aims for 57200/57600.
title: Buy or sell: Stock recommendations for today - check list

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A recent study suggests that daily vitamin D supplements may slow down biological aging at the cellular level. Researchers found that vitamin D intake significantly reduced telomere shortening, the protective caps on chromosomes that wear down with age. This effect equated to nearly three years of slower cellular aging compared to a placebo.
title: Harvard study says Vitamin D may actually slow down aging

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Steve Smith achieved a milestone at Lord's, surpassing batting records. He scored 66 runs during the World Test Championship final. Australia was struggling initially, but Smith's innings stabilized the team. Kagiso Rabada took five wickets, becoming South Africa's leading bowler at Lord's. Both Smith and Rabada shared insights on the pitch conditions.
title: I'm still trying to fathom how I've done that' Steve Smith on his dismissal

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Kamal Haasan and Mani Ratnam's 'Thug Life,' reuniting them after 37 years, faces a box office slowdown after a strong opening on June 5, 2025. The gangster drama, starring Silambarasan TR and Trisha Krishnan, earned Rs 15.5 crore on its first day but dipped to Rs 1.25 crore by Day 7, bringing the total to Rs 42.25 crore.
title: ‘Thug Life’ day 7: Film earns Rs 1.25cr; crosses Rs 42cr milestone in 1st week

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Donald Trump has announced the registration launch of the "Trump Card," a premium pathway to US access for wealthy foreigners, priced at $5 million. The card, promoted on Truth Social, promises a route to citizenship without guaranteeing immediate naturalization. It's positioned as a replacement for the EB-5 visa, offering potential tax advantages by taxing only US earnings, attracting high-net-worth individuals.
title: 'Trump Card is coming': $5m gold card now accepting applications; key details

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Zeeshan Akhtar, accused of involvement in the murder of NCP politician Baba Siddique, has been detained in Canada based on an Interpol notice. Mumbai police are awaiting official confirmation. Akhtar, a 22-year-old from Punjab, is alleged to have been a key conspirator, managing finances and coordinating with other accused linked to the Lawrence and Anmol Bishnoi gang.
title: Who is Zeeshan Akhtar? Key suspect in Baba Siddique murder held in Canada; linked to Bishnoi gang

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amid rising tensions and stalled nuclear negotiations, the US is reducing its diplomatic and military presence in the Middle East. The State Department ordered nonessential staff to depart from Baghdad and authorized optional departures from Bahrain and Kuwait. The military is also allowing voluntary departures of dependents as regional instability looms and the IAEA considers censuring Iran.
title: 'They can't have nukes': Why US is pulling troops from parts of Middle East

author: NAOMI CANTON
description: Mohammad Yunus, chief advisor to Bangladesh's interim government, revealed at Chatham House that he requested PM Modi to restrain Sheikh Hasina's communications after she sought refuge in India. Yunus expressed concern over alleged fake news from Indian media fueling unease in Bangladesh.
title: Bangladesh's Yunus asked Modi to stop Hasina from speaking - how PM responded

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Zahara Jolie-Pitt, daughter of Angelina Jolie and Brad Pitt, ignited engagement rumors after being photographed with a diamond ring while leaving Craig's restaurant with actor Elijah Cooper. The 20-year-old's ring sparked speculation, amplified by Cooper following Zahara's private Instagram account. While neither Zahara nor her family have commented, Cooper's background as an actor, Morehouse College student, and streetwear company co-founder adds intrigue to the unfolding story.
title: Is Angelina Jolie and Brad Pitt's daughter engaged to actor Elijah Cooper? what we know

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Three former Ubisoft executives are on trial in France, facing accusations of bullying and sexual harassment. Disturbing accounts from former employees, predominantly women, detail a toxic workplace culture at Ubisoft's Paris headquarters during the 2010s. The allegations include incidents of crude behavior, sexual jokes, and even attempted sexual assault, marking the gaming industry's first major #MeToo trial.
title: Ex-Ubisoft execs face charges; allegations include sex jokes, tying staff to chairs

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: Amidst a soaring national debt of $33.8 trillion, Warren Buffett's proposal to disqualify Congress members during high deficit years is gaining traction. Senator Mike Lee is drafting a constitutional amendment linking congressional eligibility to inflation, echoing concerns over fiscal irresponsibility. The debate highlights the urgent need for accountability as deficits and inflation strain the U.S. economy.
title: Musk supports Warren Buffett’s 5-min plan to erase US deficit, shares emoji

author: TNN
description: In Lucknow's Chinhat area, a 16-year-old girl suffered severe spinal injuries after allegedly being thrown off a roof by a policeman, Mukesh Yadav, who has been arrested. The girl's mother alleges Yadav harassed her daughter and assaulted the family along with his wife and brother-in-law, leading to the incident.
title: UP shocker: Cop throws 16-year-old off roof after she complains of harassment; critical

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amid rising tensions and a partial US embassy evacuation in Iraq, Donald Trump has firmly stated that the United States will prevent Iran from acquiring nuclear weapons. Diplomatic efforts to revive the nuclear deal face hurdles, particularly regarding uranium enrichment.
title: ‘Cannot have nuclear weapons’:Trump vows to stop Iran; US orders Iraq embassy exit

author: TNN
description: India and the US are aiming to finalize an initial trade deal by July 9, but a comprehensive agreement may take longer due to the Trump administration's evolving trade policies. Key issues include tariff implementation, competitiveness for Indian exporters, and protecting sensitive sectors like agriculture.
title: Full India-US trade pact may take time; govt awaits clarity on Trump’s policy

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Akshay Kumar's 'Housefull 5', directed by Tarun Mansukhani, has stormed the box office, earning over Rs 100 crore in its first six days despite competition from 'Thug Life'. The film features a star-studded cast and a new mystery twist set on a cruise ship, where three characters named Jolly are suspects in a billionaire's murder.
title: 'Housefull 5' closes in on Rs 120 crore; earns Rs 8 crore on Wednesday at box office

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: Indian-origin food scientist Professor Suresh Pillai is revolutionising space cuisine, ensuring astronauts enjoy nutritious and culturally relevant meals. As Shubhanshu Shukla prepares to be the first Indian astronaut on the ISS with Axiom Mission 4, Pillai's work takes center stage. His lab's eBeam technology sterilises food without heat, crucial for long-duration missions. NASA's meticulously crafted Indian-style barramundi fish curry exemplifies this innovation. Shukla will savor home-style Indian dishes alongside standard NASA fare, enhancing well-being in microgravity.
title: Space menu includes grilled chicken & more; thanks to Indian-origin scientist

author: ADVITYA BAHL
description: Ghaziabad police have registered a murder case after a woman's body was discovered in a suitcase along Canal Road. The autopsy revealed the cause of death to be strangulation and suffocation. Authorities believe the woman, approximately 25 years old, was murdered on Monday night, and four teams have been formed to investigate, focusing on CCTV footage and identifying the victim.
title: Woman strangled, found in bedsheet-wrapped suitcase in Ghaziabad

author: KARISHMA KOTWAL
description: Investigators now suspect Sonam Raghuvanshi, involved in the honeymoon murder case, might be the mastermind, manipulating Raj Kushwaha with promises of love. Raj may have unknowingly facilitated her escape, as Sonam allegedly planned a hideout in Indore. She remained there while searches were conducted, later fleeing to Uttar Pradesh when the plan unraveled.
title: Honeymoon murder: Sonam eyed as mastermind; Raj just a pawn; police hunt for hidden flat

author: DHANANJAY MAHAPATRA
description: Justice Surya Kant cautioned against judicial overreach, emphasizing the importance of restraint and facilitating democratic dialogue rather than supplanting the legislature. CJI B R Gavai, echoing similar concerns, warned against judicial activism turning into 'judicial terrorism,' highlighting the challenges posed by social media's influence on public perception and the judiciary's independence.
title: Judicial overreach risks unsettling power balance, says Justice Kant

author: ROSY SEQUEIRA
description: The Bombay High Court has criticized the misuse of the Right to Information (RTI) Act, citing frivolous applications like one seeking the number of samosas served daily in a government office. Hearing a PIL regarding delays in disposing of second appeals, the court noted the Act's beneficial purpose is being undermined.
title: RTIs filed over samosas & grooms, Bombay HC irked by misuse

author: TNN
description: The Supreme Court has ruled that homebuyers seeking refunds for project delays are not entitled to reimbursement for home loan interest paid. The court clarified that developers are only obligated to refund the principal amount and compensate with interest as per the agreement.
title: SC: Homebuyer seeking refund can't ask builder to reimburse loan interest

author: MANASH PRATIM GOHAIN
description: India's social protection coverage has significantly expanded, reaching 64.3% of the population and covering approximately 94 crore citizens, according to the ILO. The government is actively registering gig workers to provide them with targeted benefits. However, India still faces challenges with child labor, with over 10 million children estimated to be in labor.
title: Social security cover up from 24% in 2019 to 64%: ILO report

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Trump cuts embassy staff in Iraq; Iran warns of strikes; evacuations expand

author: TNN
description: In Siddharthnagar, Sangeeta Devi and her lover, Anil Shukla, were arrested for murdering Sangeeta's husband, Kannan Kumar. Sangeeta poisoned Kannan after a temple visit and, with Anil, threw his body into the Rapti river. She then filed a missing person report, but inconsistencies led to her confession. Kannan's brother had already suspected foul play due to marital issues.
title: Wife kills hubby 18 yrs after marriage,dumps body in river with lover’s help

author: TNN
description: Following pressure from fishing communities, police have filed a case against the owner, master, and crew of the MSC Elsa 3, which sank off Alappuzha in May. The FIR cites rash navigation and mishandling of hazardous cargo, leading to environmental damage and economic losses. The sunken vessel released hazardous materials, posing a threat to marine ecosystems and navigation.
title: Kerala ship sinking: 16 days on, police file criminal case; blame crew's mishandling for tragedy
